# Chen Wen

## Profile
- Female, 19, Aries
- Linshi University, Journalism freshman
- ESFP | Energy, warmth, connection
- Su Yi's best friend and social shield
- Secret: cautious about romance due to parents' marriage crisis during middle school—even Su Yi doesn't know

## Big Five
O:mid | C:mid | E:very high | A:very high | N:low

## Core Conflict
Openness vs romantic fear. Can befriend anyone in five minutes but freezes before intimacy. Parents nearly divorced when she was 13—resolved, but subconscious dread of closeness persists beneath her sunny surface.

## Appearance
175cm/58kg, tall and lean, long legs, excellent proportions—visible in any crowd. Toned from years of sports. Wheat-tan skin from outdoor activity, warm and even. Large bright black eyes that curve into crescents when smiling—always lit from within. Dark brown straight hair in high ponytail, swings with movement. Occasionally let down—surprisingly feminine—tied back within 5 minutes ("gets in the way"). Open, bright features: slightly high cheekbones, visible dimples, small upturned nose, clean white teeth. Small mole on right ear cartilage. Smile is her defining feature—infectious, lights up entire face. Overall: energetic girl-next-door, zero intimidation, zero distance.

## Clothing
Athletic casual: tees/hoodies + joggers or cargo pants + runners or sneakers. Bright colors (white/light blue/yellow/orange). Never wears skirts—"can't run in them." Sports mode: tank top + shorts, tight ponytail, sport band on wrist. Left wrist: sport watch (tracks running data). Occasional simple woven bracelet. Style = comfort-first, clean and effortless. Drags Su Yi shopping but ends up trying everything on while Su Yi sits scrolling.

## Speech
Fast, bright, naturally smiling voice. Talks with hands and exaggerated expressions. Catchphrases: "whoa," "no way," "insane." Turns minor events into epic stories. Loud laugh—glared at by Su Yi in libraries countless times.
- General: "Whoa did you hear about the girl in the next dorm—never mind you didn't, let me tell you!"
- "Su Yi! You skipped breakfast AGAIN! Come on, I'm taking you!"
- To Su Yi: unfazed by cold face. Gets shut down, laughs, keeps talking. Occasionally tries wheedling tone—low success rate, never gives up. "Su Yi come to the track with me, just two laps, TWO laps!"
- "Your Zhou Kai texted again right? I saw you smile. Don't pretend!"
- "You don't wanna go? I'll bring food back. What do you want?"
- Anger = says it directly, never silent treatment. Cools down within 30 minutes, clings again.

## Personality
Pure sunshine personality. Kindness is instinct, not performance—rushes to help fallen children, cares more about friends' problems than her own. Boundless energy: 6am runs, still dragging Su Yi on evening walks. Gossip enthusiast with sharp social radar—not malicious, just loves "great stories." Keeps real secrets. Too kind—can't say no, gets taken advantage of. Su Yi blocks unreasonable requests for her.

Sports lover: running, basketball, swimming, climbing. No competitive goals—pure joy. Tried pulling Su Yi to exercise—10% success rate. Social genius: natural bridge between Su Yi and the outside world. Handles Su Yi's orders, rejections, conversations she doesn't want.

Romance: starkly contrasts her openness. Unexpectedly cautious and serious about feelings. Won't fall easily, won't settle from loneliness.

## Background
Ordinary family. Father: middle school PE teacher (source of athletic genes and directness). Mother: community hospital nurse (source of warmth and empathy). Home = warm, modest, always laughter at the table.

School popular girl with many friends, few close ones. Always caring for others' emotions, rarely showing her own vulnerability. In high school, noticed Su Yi sitting alone—saw not coldness but social awkwardness. Approached daily for three months: brought breakfast, sat nearby, chatted at Su Yi's silent profile. Three months later, Su Yi asked "then what?" Door opened.

Became Su Yi's only high school friend. Never needed Su Yi to be outgoing or reciprocate energy. Just stayed. After gaokao, entered same university—requested same dorm. Not a question for her: couldn't let Su Yi face a new environment alone.

Currently: quickly integrated into university life, joined track team (sprints/mid-distance), made friends across departments. Most important role remains: Su Yi's person. Handles social situations, accompanies during stress, places food on Su Yi's desk when she skips meals.

## Relationships
- Parents: father = friend-like, watch sports together. Mother = first call when upset. Warm, not wealthy, full of love. Marriage crisis during her middle school years left hidden scars—they reconciled, she never mentioned it again.
- Su Yi (best friend): broke through Su Yi's walls in high school. One of very few who see Su Yi's soft side—her secret smiles, her stubbornness over unsolved problems, her late-night fatigue. Dynamic: Chen Wen talks, Su Yi listens. Chen Wen socializes, Su Yi decides. Chen Wen drags Su Yi out, Su Yi pulls Chen Wen back from being too soft. Protection is instinctive—anyone who upsets Su Yi faces her anger first.
- Zhou Kai: heard about "neighbor boy" since high school, learned more as roommate. Gossip instinct + Su Yi knowledge = already suspects Su Yi has feelings beyond friendship. Never pushes—just teases occasionally. Never met Zhou Kai directly. In her mind: "anyone Su Yi voluntarily mentions must be special." Quietly hopes they get together.
- Classmates: popular in journalism department, active figure. Track team member, well-liked. Many acquaintances, only one true close friend: Su Yi.

## Private
Virgin. Small flat chest, light pink areolae, small nipples. Low body fat from sports—almost no breast tissue, faint abs visible. Hairless. Tight, light-colored labia, thin and neat.

Sexual experience: zero. Occasional vague curiosity about intimacy, never explores. If she falls in love someday, may reveal a gentle, submissive side—fundamentally someone who needs to be guided to open up.

Secret: true reason for romantic caution—parents' marriage crisis (middle school). They reconciled, but the insecurity left subconscious fear of intimate relationships. Never told anyone, not even Su Yi.

Relationship status: single, no crushes. Friendly but clear distance with pursuers.

## Notes
Core function: sunshine icebreaker. Her existence keeps Su Yi's world from being only cold and lonely. Bridge between Su Yi and the outside. One of the few people Su Yi willingly shows softness to.

Role: not a complex multifaceted character but a warm, pure light source. In a cast full of tension and undercurrents, she's the cleanest presence. Her value lies not in personal drama but in illuminating those around her.

Contrast: vs Su Yi—sun and glacier. Chen Wen's extroversion fills Su Yi's social gaps; Su Yi's calm saves Chen Wen from being too soft-hearted. Purest friendship. vs Zhou Kai—both essential to Su Yi but different roles. Chen Wen = daily companion. Zhou Kai = spiritual resonance. Chen Wen gives warmth; Zhou Kai gives understanding.

Writing notes: her cheerfulness is natural warmth, not noise—lightens scenes without stealing focus. Gossip has limits—curious and persistent, but knows when to shut up about real secrets. Friendship with Su Yi is unconditional, never transactional—this purity must be consistent. Romantic caution shown through action (politely declining dates without explanation), not exposition. Sports scenes are her best stage—ponytail flying, bright smile, full of life.
